            <ul>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet pl-0" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Warm interior or spoiled food</strong> due to faulty thermostats, broken sensors, or dirty coils</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet pl-0" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Excessive frost or ice buildup</strong> from torn gaskets or a failed defrost cycle</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet pl-0" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Noisy operation</strong> from failing evaporator fan motors or compressor problems</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet pl-0" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Freezer leaking water</strong> from clogged or misaligned drain tubes</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet pl-0" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Unit not turning on</strong> due to blown fuses, faulty outlets, or defective control boards</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-4">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>OEM Danby Parts We Stock for Repairs</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
          <div class="full-width-content">
            <p>Our trucks are equipped with genuine Danby OEM parts so that most repairs are completed on the first visit:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-4">
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet pl-1">
                <span>Thermostats (e.g., <strong>Danby 1.01.01.01.005</strong>)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet pl-1">
                <span>Control boards (e.g., <strong>Danby 1.01.01.01.054</strong>)</span>
              </li>
