              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] no-bullet pl-1">
                You approve the estimate and pay a deposit
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] no-bullet pl-1">
                Parts installed and freezer tested
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] no-bullet pl-1">
                Digital invoice and post-repair care tips provided
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] no-bullet pl-1">
                Get 10% off your next repair with us
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-8">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) – Danby Freezer Repair</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
            <div class="full-width-content">
            <Accordion variant='splitted' title="Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) – Danby Freezer Repair">
              <AccordionItem title="Why is my Danby freezer not freezing properly?">
                <p>A common cause is a malfunctioning thermostat, evaporator fan motor, or dirty condenser coils. If your unit feels warm or inconsistent, a professional diagnosis can pinpoint the exact issue.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="What causes frost buildup in my Danby freezer?">
                <p>Frost issues often stem from a damaged door seal or failed defrost system. Warm air enters the freezer and freezes on the interior walls, reducing efficiency and storage space.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="Why is my Danby freezer making loud noises?">
                <p>Unusual noises are typically due to a failing compressor or fan motor. Rattling, buzzing, or clicking sounds should be checked immediately to avoid further damage.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="My freezer is leaking water—what's the fix?">
                <p>Leaks often come from clogged or misaligned drain tubes. Clearing the blockage and resetting the drainage can usually resolve the problem.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="Should I repair or replace my Danby freezer?">
                <p>If your freezer is less than 10 years old and the sealed system is intact, repair is typically the more cost-effective option. Our technicians provide honest guidance based on condition and part availability.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
            </Accordion>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

